structured.description: A constant function `fn` that returns undefined. The function logs the value 0 to the console using the `console.log` method from the browser's developer tools API. When invoked, the function will output "0" to the console without modifying any external state or returning a result.

items.description: Defines a constant arrow function that logs "0" to the console when called. The function does not take any arguments and immediately prints the value "0" using `console.log`.
items.name: fn
